{"key":"post-5391790","value":"<?xml version=\"1.0\"?>\n<post>\n<id>5391790</id>\n<content>Start over.  First of all, ANY standing water will lower humidity.  Put your perlite in a strainer and let water run through it from the faucet.  Make sure it's completely wet.  Allow to drain for a minute or two, then dump into your terrarium.  A two inch layer will provide 99% humidity for up to three weeks, at which time you simply repeat the process for the next flush/cycle.&lt;br /&gt;RR</content>\n<name>RogerRabbit</name>\n<next>5391804</next>\n<prev>5391774</prev>\n<first>5391774</first>\n<last>5392335</last>\n<when>1142191521</when>\n<utime>03/12/06 09:25 PM</utime>\n</post>"}